Experiment 6
 
Aim:Build a blog website using media queries and Bootstrap to ensure it adapts well to different screen sizes.
 
Responsive web design ensures that a website works properly on all devices like mobile, tablet, and desktop. Bootstrap and media queries help in creating flexible layouts that adjust automatically according to screen size.
 
Algorithm
1. Create an index.html file.
2. Add Bootstrap CDN in the head section.
3. Create a navigation bar using Bootstrap.
4. Add a hero section for blog introduction.
5. Use Bootstrap grid system to create blog posts.
6. Add a sidebar section.
7. Apply media queries for custom responsiveness.
8. Add footer section.
9. Test the website on different screen sizes.
 
Program Code (index.html)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Responsive Blog</title>

<!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

<style>
       body {
           background: #f8f9fa;
       }

       .hero {
           background: #0d6efd;
color: white;
           padding: 40px;
           border-radius: 10px;
       }

       /* Media Queries */
       @media (max-width: 576px) {
           .hero h1 {
               font-size: 20px;
           }
       }

       @media (min-width: 768px) {
           .hero h1 {
               font-size: 30px;
           }
       }
</style>
</head>

<body>

<!-- Navbar -->
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-md navbar-dark bg-primary">
<div class="container">
<a class="navbar-brand" href="#">MyBlog</a>

<button class="navbar-toggler" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#menu">
<span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
</button>

<div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="menu">
<ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto">
<li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="#">Home</a></li>
<li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="#">Posts</a></li>
<li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="#">About</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</nav>

<!-- Hero Section -->
<div class="container mt-4">
<div class="hero text-center">
<h1>My Blog Website</h1>
<p>Responsive design using Bootstrap and Media Queries</p>
</div>
</div>

<!-- Main Content -->
<div class="container mt-4">
<div class="row">

<!-- Blog Posts -->
<div class="col-lg-8">
<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
<div class="card">
<imgsrc="https://via.placeholder.com/300" class="card-img-top">
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">Post 1</h5>
<p class="card-text">This is a sample blog post.</p>
<button class="btnbtn-primary">Read More</button>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
<div class="card">
<imgsrc="https://via.placeholder.com/300" class="card-img-top">
<div class="card-body">
<h5 class="card-title">Post 2</h5>
<p class="card-text">This is another blog post.</p>
<button class="btn btn-primary">Read More</button>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
</div>

<!-- Sidebar -->
<div class="col-lg-4">
<div class="card">
<div class="card-body">
<h5>About</h5>
<p>This is a responsive blog website.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
</div>

<!-- Footer -->
<footer class="bg-dark text-white text-center p-3 mt-4">
<p>&copy; 2025 MyBlog</p>
</footer>

<!-- Bootstrap JS -->
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
 
Explanation of Code
• <meta name="viewport"> → Makes website responsive
• container, row, col → Bootstrap grid system
• navbar → Responsive navigation bar
• card → Blog post layout
• @media → Adjusts design for different screen sizes
• col-md-6 → 2 columns on tablet, 1 on mobile
• col-lg-8 / col-lg-4 → Main content + sidebar layout
 
Conclusion
Bootstrap and media queries help in building responsive websites that adapt to different screen sizes, improving user experience across devices.
 

